INSTITUTIONAL_CONTEXT = {
    "1.13 Institutional Context of the Grain Marketing Board": [
        "The Grain Marketing Board operates as a pivotal institution within Zimbabwe's agricultural value chain, facilitating grain marketing, storage, and distribution activities that support national food security objectives. Its workforce requirements span technical, managerial, financial, legal, and executive competencies. Recruitment therefore must attract candidates capable of operating in a regulated environment while delivering commercial efficiency and public accountability.",
        "Organisational structure typically includes headquarters functions, regional depots, and specialised units requiring coordinated HR policies. Centralising recruitment data supports workforce planning by revealing which departments generate highest application volumes and longest time-to-fill metrics. Over time, analytics derived from the system could inform training pipelines and graduate recruitment programmes aligned with skill gaps identified during screening.",
        "Public perception of fairness in GMB hiring influences stakeholder trust among farmers, employees, and government oversight bodies. Perceived nepotism or opaque selection undermines morale and may attract negative media attention. Transparent digital workflows do not automatically guarantee fairness but provide auditable evidence that stated procedures were followed, supporting institutional legitimacy.",
        "The board's corporate identity—including logo, colour palette, and communication tone—signals stability and national purpose. Recruitment materials must therefore present a coherent visual identity. The system's branding upload features enable HR to align digital touchpoints with printed annual reports and official stationery without developer intervention for each campaign.",
        "Seasonal and emergency hiring scenarios, such as expansion of storage capacity or policy-driven recruitment drives, stress HR capacity. Automation of application capture and initial CV ranking provides breathing room for officers to focus on stakeholder coordination and interview logistics rather than repetitive data entry.",
        "Collaboration with external experts during senior appointments reflects governance norms requiring independent technical or governance assessment of candidates. The interviewer portal codifies this norm by giving external panelists structured access without permanent system accounts, reducing IT provisioning burden while preserving separation of duties between evaluators and final selectors.",
        "Institutional context also includes compliance with labour laws and public service regulations where applicable. While legal interpretation remains HR management responsibility, the system supports documentary evidence of interview dates, evaluator participation, and selection rationale through logs and mark archives.",
        "Strategic alignment with national digital economy agendas encourages public enterprises to modernise citizen-facing services. An online careers portal extends digital accessibility to job seekers in rural provinces who might otherwise incur travel costs to deliver physical application packets to urban headquarters.",
    ],
}

TECHNICAL_DEEP_DIVE = {
    "5.13 Technical Deep Dive: Key Algorithms and Data Flows": [
        "When an applicant submits a form, Flask receives multipart encoding, validates required fields, checks duplicate email per job, generates application UUID, writes curriculum vitae to uploads directory with sanitised filename prefix, constructs application dictionary with default interview score structures, appends to APPLICATIONS global, and invokes save_applications persisting JSON to disk.",
        "CV scoring begins when HR triggers screening endpoint supplying job identifier. For each pending application, the service resolves resume path, extracts textual content, tokenises job description and CV corpora, computes TF-IDF vectors, measures cosine similarity, evaluates keyword skill lists, aggregates subscores into composite percentage, and writes recommendation text summarising strengths and gaps.",
        "Interview start flow retrieves application by id, validates HR session, calls _set_active_interview updating INTERVIEWER_PANELS JSON with active_application_id and timestamp, iterates other queue members previously in_progress to awaiting_screening if evaluator completion rules satisfied, sets target application in_progress, saves panels and applications, returns enriched JSON consumed by dashboard reload logic.",
        "Score submission flow authenticates user, verifies scoring permission, blocks completed interviews, blocks inactive candidates for interviewer role, reads seven criterion integers clamping to zero-twenty range, sums to raw total, normalises to percentage of 140 maximum, upserts submission array element keyed by scorer_id, recomputes average across submissions updating interview_total and interview_average fields, calls status synchronisation helper, persists data, logs activity.",
        "Screening flow loads all queue members for job, rejects if any remain merely scheduled without interview commencement, rejects if any started candidate lacks full panel submissions listing pending names, marks eligible candidates completed with screened timestamp, sorts enriched results by interview_average descending, returns JSON ranking for HR table rendering.",
        "Selection flow filters completed candidates, sorts by average, groups ties, applies random tiebreak sample when positions insufficient for tied group, updates selected flags and statuses, timestamps selection, logs activity, returns selected candidate summaries for UI confirmation messages.",
        "Interviewer polling flow executes lightweight GET comparing client last known active_changed_at with server panel timestamp; mismatch triggers full page reload ensuring newly started candidate appears without manual refresh by panel members.",
        "These data flows demonstrate tight coupling between business policy and implementation logic, illustrating why requirements analysis and design documentation were prerequisite to coding rather than afterthoughts.",
    ],
}

