        "The introductory chapter situates the Grain Marketing Board recruitment system within broader discourses on digital transformation in public administration. While many institutions invest in financial and logistics systems first, human capital systems equally determine operational capacity. Delayed modernisation of recruitment infrastructure can create a talent bottleneck that undermines other technology investments by leaving critical posts unfilled or filled with suboptimally assessed candidates.",
